HEADWORD: Autogenetic topography
<hw>Autogenetic topography</hw>. <fld>(Phys. Geog.)</fld> <def>A system
of land forms produced by the free action of rain and streams on rocks
of uniform texture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>autogenic</ent>⟦br⟧
